#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:5
msgid "Writing Style Guide"
msgstr "서술 스타일(writing style)"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:8
msgid "Primary Goals"
msgstr "핵심 목표"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:10
msgid "The main goals for this manual are as follows."
msgstr "사용설명서가 가지는 목표는 이것들이에요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:13
msgid "User Focused"
msgstr "사용자에게 맞추기"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:13
msgid ""
"While some areas of computer graphics are highly technical, this manual "
"shall be kept understandable by non-technical users."
msgstr "컴퓨터 그래픽이라는 분야는 곳곳에서 전문적이고 기술적인 것들이 보이지만, 그런 것들에 약한 사람들도 알아듣기 쉽게 쓰여야 해요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:17
msgid "Complete"
msgstr "높은 완성도"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:16
msgid ""
"So there is a canonical source of truth for each of Blender's key areas. "
"This does not mean we have to document every small detail, but users "
"should not have to rely on searching elsewhere to find the purpose of key"
" features."
msgstr ""
"우리가 기능의 마지막 한 올까지 다 서술할 필요는 없지만, 사용자들이 중요한 기능에 대한 설명을 읽는데 잘 이해가 안 돼서 따로 "
"검색해서 하면서 알아보는 일이 없도록 해야 돼요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:22
msgid "Concise"
msgstr "간결하게"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:20
msgid ""
"Computer graphics is an incredibly interesting field, there are many "
"rules, exceptions to the rules and interesting details. Expanding into "
"details can add unnecessary content, so keep the text concise and "
"relevant to the topic at hand."
msgstr ""
"컴퓨터 그래픽은 규칙이 많고, 예외도 많아서 재밌는 거죠. 말이 장황해지면 필요없는 내용도 들어갈 테니까, 글은 간결하게 적고 "
"주제에 맞춰 주세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:29
msgid "Maintainable"
msgstr "유지보수성"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:25
msgid ""
"Keep in mind that Blender has frequent releases, so try to write content "
"that will not have to be redone the moment some small change is made. "
"This also helps a small documentation community to maintain the manual."
msgstr "블렌더는 자주 출시된다는 사실 아시죠? 작은 변화에 민감한 글은 쓰지 마세요. 사용설명서 팀은 무리해서 일하고 싶지 않답니다."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:32
msgid "Content Guidelines"
msgstr "내용 지침"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:34
msgid ""
"In order to maintain a consistent writing style within the manual, please"
" keep this page in mind and only deviate from it when you have a good "
"reason to do so."
msgstr "사용설명서의 서술은 일관적이어야 하니까, 이 페이지에 나열된 규칙들을 기억해 두고 꼭 그래야만 할 이유가 있을 때만 벗어나세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:37
#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:100
msgid "Rules of thumb:"
msgstr "규칙들"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:39
msgid "Spell checking is *strongly* recommended."
msgstr "철자는 꼼꼼히 확인하고 오타를 없애주세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:40
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Use American English (e.g: modeling and not modelling, color and not "
"colour) also for formatting numbers (e.g: 2,718.28 and not 2 718,28)."
msgstr ""
"미국 영어(american english)를 사용하세요. 예를 들어 modelling이 아니라 modeling, colour이 "
"아니라 color예요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:42
msgid "Take care about grammar, appropriate wording and use simple English."
msgstr "바른 문법과 적절한 단어를 사용하세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:43
msgid ""
"Keep sentences short and clear, resulting in text that is easy to read, "
"objective and to the point."
msgstr "문장은 짧고 분명하게, 읽기 편하게 써 주세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:44
msgid "Including why or how an option might be useful is a good idea."
msgstr "그 기능이 어디에 어떻게 유용할지 써 주는 건 건 아주 좋아요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:45
msgid ""
"If you are unsure about how a feature works, ask someone else or find out"
" who developed it and ask them."
msgstr "어떤 기능이 어떻게 돌아가는지 잘 모르겠다면, 다른 사람이나 그 기능을 만든 개발자한테 물어보세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:47
msgid "To be avoided:"
msgstr "하지 말 것들"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:49
msgid ""
"Avoid writing in first person perspective, about yourself or your own "
"opinions."
msgstr "1인칭 표현, 주관적 생각은 쓰지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:50
msgid ""
"Avoid `weasel words <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weasel_word>`__ and "
"being unnecessarily vague, e.g:"
msgstr ""
"`모호한 단어(weasel words) <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weasel_word>`__ 는 쓰지"
" 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst
msgid "\"Reloading the file will probably fix the problem\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst
msgid "\"Most people do not use this option because ...\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:54
msgid "Avoid including specific details such as:"
msgstr "지나치게 자세한 설명을 쓰지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst
msgid "\"Blender has 23 different kinds of modifiers.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst
msgid ""
"\"Enabling previews adds 65536 bytes to the size of each blend-file "
"(unless it is compressed).\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:59
msgid ""
"These details are not useful for users to memorize and they become "
"quickly outdated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:60
msgid "Avoid documenting bugs."
msgstr "버그를 쓰지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:62
msgid ""
"Blender often has 100's of bugs fixed between releases, so it is not "
"realistic to reference even a fraction of them from the manual, while "
"keeping this list up to date."
msgstr "블렌더는 배포할 때마다 100개씩은 버그를 고쳐요. 그러니까 몇 개 쓰는 건 의미가 없어요. 언젠간 사라질 것들이기도 하고요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:65
msgid ""
"Issues which are known to the developers and are not going to be resolved"
" before the next release can be documented as *Known Limitations*. In "
"some cases, it may be best to include them in the :doc:`troubleshooting "
"</troubleshooting/index>` section."
msgstr ""
"개발자들이 알고 있지만 다음 배포일까지 고쳐지지 않을 문제는 *Known Limitations* 으로 서술될 수 있어요. 명백하게 "
"도움이 되는 해결법이 있다면 :doc:`</troubleshooting/index>` 에 꼭 적어주세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:68
msgid ""
"Avoid product placements, i.e. unnecessarily promoting software or "
"hardware brands. Keep content vendor-neutral where possible."
msgstr "특정 상표나 브랜드를 언급하지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:70
msgid ""
"Avoid technical explanations about the mathematical/algorithmic "
"implementation of a feature if there is a simpler way to explain it."
msgstr "더 간단하게 설명할 수 있는데도 수학식과 알고리즘을 동원해서 전문적인 설명을 하지는 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:73
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"(E.g. explaining how mesh smoothing algorithms work is unnecessary, but "
"the blending types of a mix node do need a mathematical explanation.)"
msgstr "부드럽게 하는 알고리즘을 설명할 필요는 없지만, mix 노드처럼 이따금씩 수학적 설명이 필요한 곳도 있어요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:75
msgid ""
"Avoid repetition of large portions of text. Simply explain it once, and "
"from then on refer to that explanation."
msgstr "같은 내용을 반복해서 적지 마세요. 한 번만 말하고, 필요하다면 재언급만 하세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:77
msgid ""
"For general terminology, consider defining a ``:term:`` in the "
":doc:`glossary </glossary/index>`."
msgstr "보다 나은 소통을 위해 :doc:`glossary </glossary/index>` 에서 용어를 새롭게 정의할 수도 있어요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:78
msgid ""
"Avoid enumerations of similar options, such as listing every preset or "
"every frame rate in a select menu."
msgstr "프리셋들, 프레임수 등 아주 많은 목록을 일일이 나열하거나 비슷한 항복을 반복해서 적지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:80
msgid ""
"Their contents may be summarized or simply omitted. -- Such lists are "
"only showing what is already *obvious* in the interface and end up being "
"a lot of text to read and maintain."
msgstr "간단하게 요약될 수 있어요. 그런 것들은 블렌더 화면만 봐도 알 수 있는 것들이구요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:83
msgid ""
"Avoid documenting changes in Blender between releases, that is what the "
"release notes are for. We only need to document the current state of "
"Blender."
msgstr ""
"블렌더 버전이 바뀌면서 생긴 변화는 적지 마세요. 배포 기록(release note)이 그래서 있는 거니까요. 지금 쓰는 블렌더에 "
"대해서만 적으면 돼요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:85
msgid ""
"Unless the unit a value is measured in is obscure and unpredictable, "
"there is no need to mention it."
msgstr "단위나 값의 정확도나 신뢰도가 낮다면, 적지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:86
msgid ""
"Do not simply copy the tooltips from Blender. -- People will come to the "
"manual to learn *more* than is provided by the UI."
msgstr "블렌더의 툴팁(tooltip)을 그대로 베껴 적지 마세요. 사용설명서는 툴팁 이상의 것들을 배우기 위해 오는 곳이니까요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:89
msgid ""
"As a last resort you can add comment (which is not shown in the HTML "
"page, but useful for other editors)::"
msgstr "주석을 남기는 건 자유예요. HTML 페이지에서는 보이지 않지만, 다른 기여자님들에게는 큰 도움이 되죠."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:95
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr "용어 사전"

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:97
msgid ""
"This section is specifically about the :doc:`Glossary </glossary/index>` "
"section, where we define common terms in Blender and computer graphics."
msgstr ""
"이 섹션은 특별히 :doc:`</glossary/index>` 섹션에 대해서 다루고 있어요. 블렌더랑 컴퓨터 그래픽에서 많이 쓰이는"
" 단어들의 뜻을 찾아보는 곳이죠."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:102
msgid "Define the term before providing any further information."
msgstr "더 많은 관련 정보를 주기 전에 뜻부터 알려주세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:103
msgid ""
"Avoid using constructs such as \"it is\" or \"xyz is\" before the "
"definition."
msgstr "\"it is\"나 \"xyz is\"처럼 단어를 다시 언급하는 건 피하세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:104
msgid "Avoid repeating the term immediately or using it in the definition."
msgstr "정의에서 그 단어를 다시 쓰지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:105
msgid "Avoid adding terms not found in Blender's interface or the manual."
msgstr "블렌더의 화면(interface)이나 사용설명서에서 찾을 수 없는 단어는 추가하지 마세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:106
msgid ""
"Avoid overly long entries. If an explanation of a complex term is needed,"
" supplement with external links."
msgstr "너무 긴 설명글은 쓰지 마세요. 긴 설명이 필요하다면, 링크로 대신해주세요."

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:108
msgid ""
"Avoid duplicating documentation; if explaining the term is the primary "
"focus of another section of the manual (e.g. if the term is the name of a"
" tool), either just link to that section, or avoid creating a glossary "
"entry entirely."
msgstr ""
"중복된 서술은 안 돼요. 예를 들어 그 항목의 문서에서 이미 정의를 내리고 있거나, 기능의 이름 자체가 뜻이라면 링크를 걸어주거나 "
"아예 용어집에 추가하지 마세요."

